'''Hemp protein''' is the protein content of [[Hemp#Nutrition|hemp]] seeds. The protein in hemp seeds is made up of the two [[globulin]] types of proteins, [[edestin]] (60–80%) and [[albumin]],<ref>{{cite | title=Variability in Seed Traits in a Collection of Cannabis sativa L. Genotypes | url = | pmc=4873519 | pmid= | doi=10.3389/fpls.2016.00688 | volume= | year=2016 | journal=Frontiers in Plant Science | pages= | last1 = Galasso | first1 = Incoronata}}</ref> with edestin also being rich in the essential amino acids.<ref>{{cite journal | url=http://www.fao.org/fsnforum/sites/default/files/discussions/contributions/Hempseed_as_a_nutritional_resource-_An_overview_2.pdf | pmc= | pmid= | volume=1 | title=Hempseed as a nutritional resource: An overview | year=2004 | journal=Department of Pharmaceutical Chemistry, University of Kuopio, Finland | pages=65–72 | last1=Callaway | first1=J.C. }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | url= | pmc= | pmid=25280223 | volume= 84| title=Molecular characterization of edestin gene family in Cannabis sativa L. | year=2014 | journal=Plant Physiology and Biochemistry | pages=142–148 | last1=Docimo | first1=Teresa | doi=10.1016/j.plaphy.2014.09.011}}</ref> Hemp protein has a [[PDCAAS]] score of 0.61 (the limiting amino acid being [[lysine]], with a digestibility of 94.9%)<ref>{{cite journal | url = https://www.votehemp.com/PDF/Evaluating-the-Quality-of-Protein-from-Hemp-Seed-and-Hemp-Seed-Products-Through-the-use-of-the-Protein-Digestibility-Corrected-Amino-Acid-Score-Method.pdf | pmc= | pmid= 20977230| volume= 58| title=Evaluating the quality of protein from hemp seed (Cannabis sativa L.) products through the use of the protein digestibility-corrected amino acid score method. | year=2010 | journal=J. Agric. Food Chem. | pages= 11801–7| last1 = House | first1 = J | doi=10.1021/jf102636b}}</ref> and a [[biological value]] of 87.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}} The total proportion of [[essential amino acid]]s in hemp protein isolate, is also significantly higher than that of soy protein isolate.<ref>{{cite journal | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0308814607006358 | pmc= | pmid= | volume=107 | title=Characterization, amino acid composition and in vitro digestibility of hemp (Cannabis sativa L.) proteins | year=2008 | journal=Food Chemistry | pages=11–18 | last1=Wang | first1=Xian-Sheng | doi=10.1016/j.foodchem.2007.06.064}}</ref>
Hemp protein has also been shown to reduce oxidative stress in hypertensive rats.<ref>{{cite journal | title=A Novel Hemp Seed Meal Protein Hydrolysate Reduces Oxidative Stress Factors in Spontaneously Hypertensive Rats | pmc=4276990 | pmid= 25493943| doi=10.3390/nu6125652 | volume= 6| date=December 14, 2008 | journal=Nutrients | pages=5652–5666 | last1=Girgih | first1=Abraham }}</ref>
